# UI/UX Design Guidelines

## Material Design 3
- Use Material 3 design system for consistent theming
- Implement proper color schemes with `ColorScheme.fromSeed()`
- Use Material 3 components (AppBar, NavigationBar, etc.)
- Follow Material Design accessibility guidelines

## Responsive Design
- Design for multiple screen sizes and orientations
- Use `MediaQuery` for responsive layouts
- Implement proper breakpoints for tablets and desktop
- Test on different device sizes and orientations

## Navigation Patterns
- Use `Navigator` for screen transitions
- Implement proper back button handling
- Use `BottomNavigationBar` for main navigation
- Consider `Drawer` for secondary navigation

## Theming
- Define consistent color palette in theme
- Use `Theme.of(context)` for accessing theme data
- Implement dark/light mode support
- Create custom themes for brand consistency

## Accessibility
- Add semantic labels for screen readers
- Ensure proper contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation support
- Test with accessibility tools

## Performance Considerations
- Use `ListView.builder` for scrollable content
- Implement proper image loading and caching
- Use `RepaintBoundary` for complex widgets
- Optimize animations and transitions